{"lemma":"عَبْد","slug":"عَبْد","root":"ع.ب.د","root_slug":"ع-ب-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ب-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عَبْد","root":"عبد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":131},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27791","n27792","n27793","n27794"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%AF"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a person who is under the ownership of another, a slave, a bondservant","examples":[{"text":"وَأَنْكِحُوا ٱلْأَيَامَى مِنْكُمْ وَٱلصَّالِحِينَ مِنْ عِبَادِكُمْ وَإِمَائِكُمْ إِنْ يَكُونُوا فُقَرَاءَ يُغْنِهِمُ ٱللَّهُ مِنْ فَضْلِهِ وَٱللَّهُ وَاسِعٌ عَلِيمٌ","english":"And marry the unmarried among you and the righteous among your male slaves and female slaves. If they should be poor, Allah will enrich them from His bounty, and Allah is all-Encompassing and Knowing"},{"text":"جَمَعْتُ رُدَيْنِيًّا كَأَنَّ سِنَانَهُ / سَنَا لَهَبٍ لَمْ يَسْتَعِنْ بِدُخَانِ\n لَيَالِيَ إِذْ أَنْتُمْ لِرَهْطِيَ أَعْبُدٌ / بِرَمَّانَ لَمَّا أَجْدَبَ ٱلحَرَمَانِ","english":"I held up my Rudayni spear, its teeth like splendid, smokeless flames\nFor nights, you were bondsmen for my troop, in Ramān, when the Sanctuaries dried."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a person who is under the ownership of another, a slave, a bondservant; someone resembling, likened to, or related to a slave (as in status, worth, condition, and so on)","examples":[{"text":"أَكُلَّمَا ٱغْتَالَ عَبْدُ السَّوْءِ سَيِّدَهُ / أَوْ خَانَهُ فَلَهُ فِي مِصْرَ تَمْهِيدُ\nصَارَ الْخَصِيُّ إِمَامَ الْآبِقِينَ بِهَا / فَٱلْحُرُّ مُسْتَعْبَدٌ وَٱلْعَبْدُ مَعْبُودُ\nنَامَتْ نَوَاطِيرُ مِصْرٍ عَنْ ثَعَالِبِهَا / فَقَدْ بَشِمْنَ وَمَا تَفْنَى العَنَاقِيدُ\nالْعَبْدُ لَيْسَ لِحُرٍّ صَالِحٍ بِأَخٍ / لَوْ أَنَّهُ فِي ثِيَابِ الْحُرِّ مَوْلُودُ\nلَا تَشْتَرِ الْعَبْدَ إِلَّا وَٱلْعَصَا مَعَهُ / إِنَّ الْعَبِيدَ لَأَنْجَاسٌ مَنَاكِيدُ\nمَا كُنْتُ أَحْسَبُنِي أَحْيَا إِلَى زَمَنٍ / يُسِيءُ بِي فِيهِ كَلْبٌ وَهْوَ مَحْمُودُ","english":"Can any fiendish slave who slew or stabbed his master find in Egypt refuge, there to be advanced?\nThe Castrate King became the Chief of Runaways! The servants are revered; the freeman is disgraced!\nThe Egyptian shepherds, they all are now asleep, and foxes roam, and all were drowsed with endless grapes!\nA freeman and a slave are neither peers nor brothers, though the slave may be in freemen's clothing raised.\nNever pay for any slave without the stick too: a slave, to noble men, is foul, and vile, and damned!\nI never thought that I would live and see a dog degrading me while he himself is hailed and praised!"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"term of abuse for a black person, equivalent to English nigger","tags":["colloquial","ethnic","offensive","slur","vulgar"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to worship, to serve, to be devoted to; to venerate or adore in a subservient manner","examples":[{"text":"إِيَّاكَ نَعْبُدُ وَإِيَّاكَ نَسْتَعِينُ","english":"You alone do we worship, and from You alone do we seek help."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to enslave, to subjugate, to subject","examples":[{"text":"وَتِلۡكَ نِعۡمَةٌ تَمُنُّهَا عَلَىَّ أَنۡ عَبَّدتَّ بَنِىٓ إِسۡرَآءِيلَ","english":"\"How can that be a ‘favour,’ of which you remind me, when ˹it was only because˺ you ˹have˺ enslaved the Children of Israel?”\""}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"A Central Semitic innovation, cognate with Hebrew עֶבֶד (ʿéḇeḏ), Phoenician 𐤏𐤁𐤃 (ʿbd), Ugaritic 𐎓𐎁𐎄 (ʿbd), Classical Syriac ܥܒܕܐ (ʿaḇdā), Old South Arabian 𐩲𐩨𐩵 (ʿbd)."},"ipa":["/ʕabd/","/ʕa.ba.da/","/ʕab.ba.da/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27791","headword_ar":"عَبْدٌ","root":"Ebd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", originally an epithet, but used as a subst., (Sb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A male slave;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O, L, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mamoluwkN","text_ar":"مَمْلُوكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L, K;) [but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabodN","text_ar":"عَبْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is now generally applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a male black slave;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mamoluwkN","text_ar":"مَمْلُوكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a male white slave;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and this distinction has long obtained;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hur~N","text_ar":"حُرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, A, O, L, Msb;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabodalN","text_ar":"عَبْدَلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, K,) in which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":"is augmentative: (L:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a servant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"worshipper,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of God, and of a false god, or of the Devil: (Lth, L, &c.:) [you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eabodu A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"عَبْدُ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eabodu Al$~amosi","text_ar":"عَبْدُ الشَّمْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAbidN","text_ar":"عَابِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which signifies the same; and see the remarks in this paragraph on the pls."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabiydN","text_ar":"عَبِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EibaAdN","text_ar":"عِبَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabadapN","text_ar":"عَبَدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.:] and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a man,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"human being;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, L, K;) as being"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bondman"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marobuwbN","text_ar":"مَرْبُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to his Creator;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L;) applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a male"},{"kind":"text","text":"and to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a female;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-Hazm, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whether free or a slave:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEobudN","text_ar":"اَعْبُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEobidapN","text_ar":"اَعْبِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEobaAdN","text_ar":"اَعْبَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IKtt, TA,) [all pls. of pauc.,] of which the first is the most commonly known, (Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabiydN","text_ar":"عَبِيدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EibaAdN","text_ar":"عِبَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K,) which two and the first are the most commonly known of all the many pls. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabodN","text_ar":"عَبْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabiydN","text_ar":"عَبِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaliybN","text_ar":"كَلِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalobN","text_ar":"كَلْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a rare form of pl.; (S, O;) or, accord. to some, it is a quasipl. n.; accord. to Ibn-Málik,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylN","text_ar":"فَعِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs as a pl. measure, but sometimes they use it in the manner of a pl. and make it fem., as in the instance of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabiydN","text_ar":"عَبِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and sometimes they use it in the manner of quasi-pl. ns. and make it masc., as in the instances of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HajiyjN","text_ar":"حَجِيجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaliybN","text_ar":"كَلِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (MF;) [accord. to the general and more approved opinion, it is a quasi-pl. n., and therefore fem. and masc., but most commonly fem.;] and further it should be remarked that the common people agree in making a difference between"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabiydN","text_ar":"عَبِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EibaAdN","text_ar":"عِبَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", by the former meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slaves"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and by the latter meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"servants"},{"kind":"text","text":"of God and also simply, with the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mankind"},{"kind":"text","text":"], saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`w^ulaA='i EabiydN","text_ar":"هٰوُلَا=ءِ عَبِيدٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"these are slaves,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA EabodN mino EibaAdi A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"هٰذَا عَبْدٌ مِنْ عِبَادِ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"this is a servant, of the servants of God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Az, L:) [and a distinction is also made between"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EibaAdN","text_ar":"عِبَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabadapN","text_ar":"عَبَدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", respecting which see what follows:] other pls. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabodN","text_ar":"عَبْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EubodaAnN","text_ar":"عُبْدَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tumoraAnN","text_ar":"تُمْرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamorN","text_ar":"تَمْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EibodaAnN","text_ar":"عِبْدَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiHo$aAnN","text_ar":"جِحْشَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaHo$N","text_ar":"جَحْشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EubudN","text_ar":"عُبُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suqufN","text_ar":"سُقُفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saqofN","text_ar":"سَقْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,) or this is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabiydN","text_ar":"عَبِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rugufN","text_ar":"رُغُفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ragiyfN","text_ar":"رَغِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Zj,) and is also a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAbidN","text_ar":"عَابِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,) and some read [in the Kur v. 65]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eubuda AlT~aAguwti","text_ar":"عُبُدَ الطَّاغُوتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Akh, S, O,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EubodN","text_ar":"عُبْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EubuwdN","text_ar":"عُبُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eub~adN","text_ar":"عُبَّدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eub~aAdN","text_ar":"عُبَّادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabadapN","text_ar":"عَبَدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IKtt, TA,) the last three of which are also pls. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAbidN","text_ar":"عَابِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L:) one says of the worshippers of a plurality of gods,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo Eabadapu","text_ar":"هُمْ عَبَدَةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~aAguwti","text_ar":"الطَّاغُوتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they are the servants of Et-Tághoot"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; but the Muslims one calls"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EibaAdu A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"عِبَادُ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the servants,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"worshippers, of God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, L:) [all these are pls. in the proper sense of the term, of the broken class:] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaboduwna","text_ar":"عَبْدُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) a pl. of the sound class, adopted because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabodN","text_ar":"عَبْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is originally an epithet: (TA:) and [the following, with the exception of the first, and of some which are particularized as being pls. of pls., are also said to be pls., but are properly speaking quasi-pl. ns., namely,] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabudN","text_ar":"عَبُدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) accord. to some, who read [in the Kur ubi suprà]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eabuda AlT~aAguwti","text_ar":"عَبُدَ الطَّاغُوتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", making the former a prefixed noun, as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the servants"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadam","text_ar":"خَدَم"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of Et-Tághoot;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but it is a n. of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEulN","text_ar":"فَعُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ha*urN","text_ar":"حَذُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nadusN","text_ar":"نَدُسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", not a pl.; the meaning being"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the servant"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAdim","text_ar":"خَادِم"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of Et- Tághoot;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Akh, S, O;) and it is also used by poetic license for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabodN","text_ar":"عَبْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Fr, T, S, O;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eibid~aAnN","text_ar":"عِبِدَّانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eibid~aA='u","text_ar":"عِبِدَّا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eibid~aY","text_ar":"عِبِدَّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, K;) or, accord. to some, the last of these signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slaves born in a state of slavery;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female"},{"kind":"text","text":"is termed ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabodapN","text_ar":"عَبْدَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and Lth says that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eibid~aY","text_ar":"عِبِدَّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a number of slaves born in a state of slavery, generation after generation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but Az says that this is a mistake, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eibid~aY A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"عِبِدَّى ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EbaAdu A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"عبَادُ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", that it is thus used in a trad., and that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eibid~aY","text_ar":"عِبِدَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied in another trad. to poor men of the class called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aholu AlS~uf~ap","text_ar":"اَهْلُ الصُّفَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eubud~aA='u","text_ar":"عُبُدَّا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eibid~apN","text_ar":"عِبِدَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EibaAd~N","text_ar":"عِبَادٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKtt, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEobadapN","text_ar":"مَعْبَدَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oyaxapN","text_ar":"مَشْيَخَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, O, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEobuwdaA='u","text_ar":"مَعْبُودَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Yaakoob, S, O, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEobuwdaY","text_ar":"مَعْبُودَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IKtt, TA,) and [pl. pl.] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaAbidu","text_ar":"مَعَابِدُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) said to be pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEobadapN","text_ar":"مَعْبَدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and pl. pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEaAbidu","text_ar":"اَعَابِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEobudN","text_ar":"اَعْبُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eabiyduwna","text_ar":"عَبِيدُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Es-Suyootee, MF,) app. pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabiydN","text_ar":"عَبِيدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (MF.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA@doxuliY fiY EibaAdiY","text_ar":"فَا@دْخُلِى فِى عِبَادِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur lxxxix. 29, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Then enter thou among my righteous servants:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ksh, Bd, Jel:) or it means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY HizobiY","text_ar":"فِى حِزْبِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"among my peculiar party"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O.) ―         -b2-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ignoble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"base-born;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hur~N","text_ar":"حُرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used to signify “ generous, ” “ noble, ” or “ well-born. ” (Mgh in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hr","text_ar":"حر"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain plant, of sweet odour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the camels are fond because it makes the milk to become plentiful, and fattens; it is sharp,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hot,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAd~","text_ar":"حَادّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"O, or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAr~","text_ar":"حَارّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in temperament; and when they depasture it they become thirsty, and seek the water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA:) so says IAar. (O.)       -A3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A short and broad"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSol","text_ar":"نَصْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arrow-head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spear-head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blade"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (AA, O, * K.)"}],"source_refs":["Sb","TA","L","K","S","O","Msb","IKtt","Az","Zj","Akh","MF","Lth","T","Ksh","Bd","Jel"]},{"entry_id":"n27792","headword_ar":"عَبَدٌ","root":"Ebd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAbidN","text_ar":"عَابِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n27793","headword_ar":"عَبُدٌ","root":"Ebd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the paragraph commencing with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabodN","text_ar":"عَبْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", latter half."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n27794","headword_ar":"عَبِدٌ","root":"Ebd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAbidN","text_ar":"عَابِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(but the latter is rarely used, Ibn-'Arafeh)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Angry."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) And (both words)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Disdaining,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disdainful; scorning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scornful."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) Accord. to AA,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaAbidiyna","text_ar":"العَابِدِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the words of the Kur [xliii. 81],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ino kaAna lilr~aHom`ni waladN faA^anaA A^aw~alu","text_ar":"اـِنْ كَانَ لِلرَّحْمٰنِ وَلَدٌ فَاَنَا اَوَّلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaAbidiyna","text_ar":"العَابِدِينَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The disdainers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scorners,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the angry:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * L:) but Ibn-'Arafeh rejects this assertion: (TA:) these words are variously explained; as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is not to the Compassionate a son; and I am the first of the angry disdainers"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scorners"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the assertion that there is: or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and I am the first of the deniers"},{"kind":"text","text":"of this assertion: or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and I am the first of the worshippers"},{"kind":"text","text":"of God according to the unitarian doctrine, or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the worshippers of God"},{"kind":"text","text":"of this people: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"if there were to the Compassionate a son, I would be the first of"},{"kind":"text","text":"his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"worshippers:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"if there be to the Compassionate a son, I am the first of worshippers;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but I am not the first worshipper of God: or, accord. to Az, the best interpretation is one ascribed to Mujáhid; i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"if there be to the Compassionate a son"},{"kind":"text","text":"in your opinion,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am the first of those who have worshipped"},{"kind":"text","text":"God alone, and who have thus charged you with uttering a falsehood in this your assertion. (L.)"}],"source_refs":["TA"]}]}}